Notes:

To access git bash on a project, simply right click the main folder of project then select git bash

to create a file using git bash "touch index.html"

to initialize the git on your project "git init" - this will create .git folder but by default, you can not see it because it is hidden.

BEFORE START ADD NAME AND EMAIL TO GIT
git config --global user.name 'Gab Adawag'
git config --global user.email 'me@gadawag.com'

TO ADD A FILE TO GIT REPOSITORY
git add index.html //add specific file
git add *.html //add all html file
git add . //will add all files


TO SEE WHAT IS IN THE STAGING AREA
git status


TO COMMIT
git commit -m 'Changed app.js' or index.html whatever file you want to COMMIT



TO EXCLUDE FILES ON git add .
create a file .gitignore then type inside that which file you want to ignore



TO CREATE A NEW BRANCH
git brach login

TO SWITCH BRANCH
git checkout login


//TO PUBLISH THE CHANGES TO GITHUB REPOSITORY
git push


//TO MAKE UPDATE THE PROJECT FROM REPOSITORY (don't forget to register first the target repository using "git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repositoryname.git")
git pull




GENERAL STEPS:

1. Access the project using git bash (right-click the folder then choose gitbash)
2. Initialize the project using "git init"
3. If you made some changes on files use "git status" to check the affected and ready to staged files.
4. Staged the files (add them to local repository) using "git add"
5. Commit the staged file (save on local repository) using git commit -m 'put your comment here'
6. If there are nothing else to do, upload the project on github repository
  6.1 First, add the remote repository target using "git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repositoryname.git"
  6.2 Then push the updated project using "git push -u origin master"
